Name: Block
Text Area 1:
To format shapes as you'd like, click on a shape and then click "Shape Options"     , "Fill Color"      , and "Line Color"    on the properties bar at the top of the canvas. 
Hover over a shape and click on any red circle    to add lines.
Add text to a line by double-clicking the text or anywhere on the line and typing.
To format lines, click on a line use the properties bar at the top of the canvas.

Pro tip: This UML deployment diagram models a very high-level overview of a basic e-commerce web application with the option to toggle to a lower level overview via the "Toggle Overview" blue button.
